a1=A.a([A.V(v5,d9),A.V(v6,"CTS typically spares the palm (Palmar Cutaneous branch branches off proximal to the carpal tunnel) and usually causes nocturnal symptoms; here the palm is involved and symptoms are activity-related."),A.V(v7,"AIN syndrome is a PURE MOTOR syndrome causing weakness in FPL/FDP2; it would NOT cause the palmar numbness seen here."),A.V(v8,"Radiculopathy would involve C6 muscles like the Brachioradialis and would typically be associated with neck pain and decreased brachioradialis reflex."),A.V("Medial Epicondylitis (Golfer's Elbow)","Causes pain at the medial epicondyle on palpation and resisted wrist flexion, but NOT the neurological sensory loss in the palm.")],ae9)
