b4=A.ce(ab4,b6,k0,"INDICATED (Look for demyelination)",A.a([A.t(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,g9,h0,f0,h4,h1,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,h5,h6,f0,h4,h1,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,h8,h9,f0,h4,i0,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,l5,l6,f0,h4,l7,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m0,l6,f0,h4,m1,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m2,q6,f0,h4,m1,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m4,m5,f0,h4,m6,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m7,m8,f0,h4,q8,f0)],n),"Acute, rapidly progressive ascending symmetric weakness with global areflexia and antecedent gastrointestinal illness. Diagnosis is supported by NCS findings of demyelination (delayed motor latencies, slow conduction, and absent/prolonged F-waves) and CSF albuminocytologic dissociation.",b5,"gbs",b7,ae8,ae7,!0,b4,A.a(["In early GBS (AIDP), the 'Sural-sparing' pattern (abnormal motor, normal sural) is a classic finding.","Absent or prolonged F-waves and H-reflexes are often the earliest signs of demyelination as they sample the long course of the nerve/roots.","Areflexia in the face of only mild weakness is a clinical red flag for a demyelinating polyneuropathy like GBS."],af3),"Ascending Weakness and Tingling")
ae7=A.cd(58,"Proximal leg weakness and dry mouth, improvement with activity",i1,"Develop progressive difficulty climbing stairs and rising from chairs. Interestingly, the first few steps are the hardest, and strength seems to improve slightly with walking. Noticed dry mouth (xerostomia) and constipation. Long history of smoking.","Tiotropium, Lisinopril","Construction","COPD, Hypertension")
ae8=A.ch("Mild proximal muscle thinning.",x6,"1+ (diminished) at the patella; however, they become 2+ (normal) immediately after brief exercise (reflex potentiation).",x6,x6,"Post-exercise potentiation of reflexes and strength.","Proximal hip flexors 3/5 initially. After 10 seconds of maximal isometric contraction, strength improves to 4/5.")
b7=A.a([A.V(aa8,d9),A.V("Myasthenia Gravis (MG)","MG usually involves ocular/bulbar muscles first and DOES NOT typically show baseline low CMAPs or significant facilitation after exercise. Reflexes are also normal in MG."),A.V("Polymyositis / Dermatomyositis","Inflammatory myopathies cause constant weakness (doesn't improve with exercise) and are associated with significantly elevated CK; they do not show the CMAP facilitation seen here."),A.V("Statin-induced Myopathy","Usually presents with myalgia and elevated CK; would not show autonomic symptoms or areflexia/reflex potentiation."),A.V(ab2,"Would cause UMN signs (Babinski, spasticity) and would not have dry mouth or the specific NCS facilitation pattern.")],ae9)
b5=A.a5(["constitutional","15-lb unintentional weight loss. Chronic cough (former smoker).","musculoskeletal","Proximal limb weakness, especially in the legs. No joint pain.","neurological","Weakness improving with exercise. Dry mouth. Chronic constipation. Normal sensation."],af1,af1)
b6=A.a(["Voltage-Gated Calcium Channel (VGCC) Antibody: Positive","Creatine Kinase (CK): 280 U/L (Mildly Elevated)"],af3)
